─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
WHEN IS PANEL 2 VISIBLE?
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VISIBLE on:
✓ Individual membership pages (e.g., /dashboard/mastering-the-trade)
✓ Course detail pages
✓ Any page that needs contextual sub-navigation

HIDDEN on:
✗ Main dashboard landing page (/dashboard)
  └─ CSS Rule (Line 2451): .page-id-401190 .dashboard__content-sidebar { display: none; }
✗ Simple pages without sub-navigation
✗ Mobile devices (< 1080px)

RESPONSIVE BEHAVIOR:
├─ Desktop (1080px+): Visible when applicable
└─ Mobile/Tablet (<1080px): Always hidden (display: none)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
[SECTION 4] THE COLLAPSE BEHAVIOR - HOW PANELS SWITCH
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

IMPORTANT: The panels DO NOT "collapse" or "switch" in the traditional sense.
Instead, they work on a VISIBILITY SYSTEM based on the page you're viewing.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[4.1] ON THE MAIN DASHBOARD PAGE (/dashboard)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

LAYOUT:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                       │
│  [PANEL 1: PRIMARY]     [MAIN CONTENT - FULL WIDTH]                 │
│  280px                  Remaining space                              │
│  Blue sidebar           ├─ Dashboard header                          │
│  Always visible         ├─ Membership cards                          │
│                         ├─ Tools section                             │
│                         └─ Weekly Watchlist featured                 │
│                                                                       │
│                         [PANEL 2: HIDDEN]                            │
│                         CSS: display: none                           │
│                                                                       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

WHY PANEL 2 IS HIDDEN:
The main dashboard doesn't need contextual navigation because it's showing
an overview of ALL memberships. There's no specific membership context.

CSS RULE (Line 2451-2453):
.page-id-401190 .dashboard__content-sidebar {
    display: none;
}

WHERE:
├─ .page-id-401190 = WordPress page ID for main dashboard
└─ This rule specifically hides Panel 2 on the landing page

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[4.2] ON AN INDIVIDUAL MEMBERSHIP PAGE (/dashboard/mastering-the-trade)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

LAYOUT:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                                       │
│  [PANEL 1]         [MAIN CONTENT]              [PANEL 2]            │
│  280px             Flexible width               260px               │
│  Blue sidebar      ├─ Membership header        White sidebar        │
│  Still visible     ├─ Content sections         ├─ Sub-menu          │
│                    ├─ Videos/lessons           ├─ Quick links       │
│                    └─ Resources                └─ Related items     │
│                                                                       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

WHY PANEL 2 IS VISIBLE:
Individual membership pages need contextual navigation to help users find
specific content within that membership (lessons, videos, resources, etc.)

CSS RULE:
No .page-id-401190 class on these pages, so the display: none rule doesn't apply.
Panel 2 is visible by default on membership pages.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[4.3] THE "COLLAPSE" IS ACTUALLY A PAGE TRANSITION
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

WHAT HAPPENS WHEN USER CLICKS A MEMBERSHIP:

STEP 1: User is on main dashboard (/dashboard)
├─ Panel 1: Visible (blue sidebar)
├─ Panel 2: Hidden (CSS display: none)
└─ Main content: Shows all membership cards

STEP 2: User clicks "Mastering the Trade" membership card
├─ Browser navigates to: /dashboard/mastering-the-trade
├─ New page loads
└─ Page has different WordPress page ID (not 401190)

STEP 3: New page renders with different layout
├─ Panel 1: Still visible (blue sidebar - same as before)
├─ Panel 2: NOW VISIBLE (no display: none rule applies)
└─ Main content: Shows membership-specific content

STEP 4: Panel 2 appears on the right side
├─ Shows sub-navigation for "Mastering the Trade"
├─ Lists lessons, videos, resources
└─ Provides quick access to membership sections

THIS IS NOT A COLLAPSE - IT'S A PAGE CHANGE!
The "collapse" behavior you see is actually:
1. Page navigation (URL changes)
2. New HTML loads
3. Different CSS rules apply
4. Panel 2 becomes visible because display: none rule doesn't apply

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
[SECTION 5] COMPLETE FLOW - STEP-BY-STEP USER JOURNEY
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Let's walk through the COMPLETE user experience from login to viewing
membership content, explaining exactly when each panel appears.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[5.1] USER LOGS IN
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ACTION: User enters email/password and clicks "Login"

WHAT HAPPENS:
1. WordPress authenticates user
2. Browser redirects to: /dashboard
3. Main dashboard page loads

PANELS VISIBLE:
├─ Panel 1 (Primary): ✓ VISIBLE
│   └─ Shows all memberships user has access to
└─ Panel 2 (Secondary): ✗ HIDDEN
    └─ CSS rule hides it: .page-id-401190 .dashboard__content-sidebar { display: none; }

SCREEN LAYOUT:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [PANEL 1 - 280px]      [MAIN CONTENT - Full Width]                  │
│                                                                       │
│ Profile: John Doe      MEMBER DASHBOARD                             │
│                        ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐            │
│ Member Dashboard       │ Mastering    │ │ Simpler      │            │
│ My Classes             │ the Trade    │ │ Showcase     │            │
│ My Indicators          └──────────────┘ └──────────────┘            │
│                                                                       │
│ MEMBERSHIPS            TOOLS                                         │
│ • Mastering Trade      ┌──────────────┐                             │
│ • Simpler Showcase     │ Weekly       │                             │
│                        │ Watchlist    │                             │
│ MASTERY                └──────────────┘                             │
│ • Options 101                                                        │
│                        WEEKLY WATCHLIST                              │
│ TOOLS                  [Featured content section]                    │
│ • Weekly Watchlist                                                   │
│ • Support                                                            │
│                                                                       │
│ ACCOUNT                                                              │
│ • My Account                                                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[5.2] USER VIEWS MEMBERSHIP CARDS
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ACTION: User sees membership cards in main content area

WHAT USER SEES:
Each membership card shows:
├─ Membership icon (50px circle with colored background)
├─ Membership name (e.g., "Mastering the Trade")
└─ Two action buttons:
    ├─ "Dashboard" → Goes to membership dashboard
    └─ "Trading Room" → Opens live trading room (new tab)

PANELS STATUS:
├─ Panel 1: Still visible (unchanged)
└─ Panel 2: Still hidden (unchanged)

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[5.3] USER CLICKS "DASHBOARD" ON A MEMBERSHIP CARD
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ACTION: User clicks "Dashboard" button on "Mastering the Trade" card

WHAT HAPPENS:
1. Browser navigates to: /dashboard/mastering-the-trade
2. WordPress loads new page
3. Page has different ID (not 401190)
4. CSS display: none rule NO LONGER APPLIES
5. Panel 2 becomes visible

PANELS VISIBLE:
├─ Panel 1 (Primary): ✓ STILL VISIBLE
│   └─ Same content as before (all memberships listed)
└─ Panel 2 (Secondary): ✓ NOW VISIBLE
    └─ Shows sub-navigation for "Mastering the Trade"

SCREEN LAYOUT:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [PANEL 1]         [MAIN CONTENT]              [PANEL 2 - 260px]     │
│ 280px             Flexible                    White sidebar         │
│                                                                       │
│ Profile: John     MASTERING THE TRADE         NAVIGATION            │
│                                                                       │
│ Member Dashboard  [Header with title]         • Overview            │
│ My Classes                                     • Lessons            │
│ My Indicators     [Content sections]           • Videos             │
│                                                • Resources          │
│ MEMBERSHIPS       ┌─────────────────┐         • Trading Room       │
│ • Mastering Trade │ Latest Lesson   │         • Support            │
│ • Simpler Show... │                 │                              │
│                   └─────────────────┘         QUICK LINKS          │
│ MASTERY                                                             │
│ • Options 101     ┌─────────────────┐         • Chart Setup        │
│                   │ Recent Video    │         • Indicators         │
│ TOOLS             │                 │         • Strategies         │
│ • Weekly Watch... └─────────────────┘                              │
│ • Support                                                           │
│                   [More content...]                                 │
│ ACCOUNT                                                             │
│ • My Account                                                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

NOTICE THE CHANGE:
├─ Panel 1: Unchanged (still shows all memberships)
├─ Panel 2: NOW VISIBLE (shows membership-specific navigation)
└─ Main content: Now shows "Mastering the Trade" specific content

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[5.4] USER NAVIGATES WITHIN MEMBERSHIP USING PANEL 2
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ACTION: User clicks "Lessons" in Panel 2 (secondary sidebar)

WHAT HAPPENS:
1. Browser navigates to: /dashboard/mastering-the-trade/lessons
2. Page updates to show lessons
3. Both panels remain visible

PANELS STATUS:
├─ Panel 1: ✓ Still visible (unchanged)
└─ Panel 2: ✓ Still visible (may highlight "Lessons" as active)

MAIN CONTENT CHANGES:
├─ Shows list of lessons for "Mastering the Trade"
├─ User can click individual lessons to watch
└─ Panel 2 provides quick navigation between sections

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[5.5] USER RETURNS TO MAIN DASHBOARD
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ACTION: User clicks "Member Dashboard" in Panel 1 (primary sidebar)

WHAT HAPPENS:
1. Browser navigates back to: /dashboard
2. Main dashboard page loads again
3. Page ID is 401190 again
4. CSS display: none rule APPLIES AGAIN
5. Panel 2 becomes hidden

PANELS VISIBLE:
├─ Panel 1: ✓ Still visible (unchanged)
└─ Panel 2: ✗ HIDDEN AGAIN
    └─ CSS rule applies: .page-id-401190 .dashboard__content-sidebar { display: none; }

SCREEN LAYOUT:
Back to the original layout with only Panel 1 visible and full-width main content.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
[SECTION 6] TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION - CSS & JAVASCRIPT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[6.1] CSS RULES THAT CONTROL PANEL VISIBILITY
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

PANEL 1 (PRIMARY SIDEBAR) - ALWAYS VISIBLE:

.dashboard__sidebar {
    display: flex;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    flex-flow: row nowrap;
    width: 280px;
    background-color: #0f2d41;
    min-height: 100%;
}

PANEL 2 (SECONDARY SIDEBAR) - DEFAULT VISIBLE:

.dashboard__content-sidebar {
    display: none;        /* Hidden on mobile by default */
    width: 260px;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    margin-top: -1px;
    border-right: 1px solid #dbdbdb;
    border-top: 1px solid #dbdbdb;
}

@media (min-width: 1080px) {
    .dashboard__content-sidebar {
        display: block;   /* Visible on desktop */
    }
}

PANEL 2 - HIDDEN ON MAIN DASHBOARD:

.page-id-401190 .dashboard__content-sidebar {
    display: none !important;
}

WHERE:
├─ .page-id-401190 = WordPress adds this class to <body> on main dashboard
├─ !important = Overrides the media query rule
└─ Result: Panel 2 is hidden on main dashboard even on desktop

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[6.2] HTML STRUCTURE
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

<div class="dashboard">
    
    <!-- PANEL 1: PRIMARY SIDEBAR (Always visible) -->
    <aside class="dashboard__sidebar">
        <nav class="dashboard__nav-primary">
            <!-- Profile section -->
            <a href="/dashboard/account" class="dashboard__profile-nav-item">
                <span class="dashboard__profile-photo"></span>
                <span class="dashboard__profile-name">John Doe</span>
            </a>
            
            <!-- Main navigation -->
            <ul>
                <li><a href="/dashboard">Member Dashboard</a></li>
                <li><a href="/dashboard/classes">My Classes</a></li>
                <li><a href="/dashboard/indicators">My Indicators</a></li>
            </ul>
            
            <!-- Memberships category -->
            <ul>
                <li><p class="dashboard__nav-category">MEMBERSHIPS</p></li>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/dashboard/mastering-the-trade">Mastering the Trade</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/dashboard/simpler-showcase">Simpler Showcase</a></li>
                </ul>
            </ul>
            
            <!-- More categories... -->
        </nav>
    </aside>
    
    <!-- MAIN CONTENT AREA -->
    <main class="dashboard__main">
        
        <!-- Dashboard header -->
        <header class="dashboard__header">
            <h1>Member Dashboard</h1>
        </header>
        
        <!-- Content wrapper -->
        <div class="dashboard__content">
            
            <!-- Main content column -->
            <div class="dashboard__content-main">
                <!-- Membership cards, content, etc. -->
            </div>
            
            <!-- PANEL 2: SECONDARY SIDEBAR (Conditional) -->
            <aside class="dashboard__content-sidebar">
                <section class="content-sidebar__section">
                    <h3>Navigation</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="#">Overview</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#">Lessons</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#">Videos</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </section>
            </aside>
            
        </div>
    </main>
    
</div>

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[6.3] JAVASCRIPT BEHAVIOR (Mobile Menu)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

On mobile (<1280px), Panel 1 is hidden by default and slides in when user
clicks the menu button.

MOBILE MENU BUTTON (Line 3157-3166):

<footer class="dashboard__toggle">
    <button class="dashboard__toggle-button" data-toggle-dashboard-menu>
        <div class="dashboard__toggle-button-icon">
            <span></span>  <!-- Hamburger line 1 -->
            <span></span>  <!-- Hamburger line 2 -->
            <span></span>  <!-- Hamburger line 3 -->
        </div>
        <span class="framework__toggle-button-label">Dashboard Menu</span>
    </button>
</footer>

OVERLAY (Line 3167):

<div class="dashboard__overlay" data-toggle-dashboard-menu></div>

JAVASCRIPT FUNCTIONALITY:
1. User clicks menu button
2. JavaScript adds class: .html--dashboard-menu-open to <html>
3. CSS shows Panel 1 with opacity: 1, visibility: visible
4. Overlay appears with rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65) background
5. User clicks overlay or menu button again to close
6. JavaScript removes .html--dashboard-menu-open class
7. Panel 1 slides out, overlay fades out

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
[SECTION 7] RESPONSIVE BEHAVIOR - MOBILE VS DESKTOP
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[7.1] DESKTOP (1280px and wider)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

PANEL 1 (PRIMARY):
├─ Always visible
├─ Fixed position on left
├─ 280px wide
└─ No menu button needed

PANEL 2 (SECONDARY):
├─ Visible on membership pages (1080px+)
├─ Hidden on main dashboard (.page-id-401190)
├─ 260px wide
└─ Fixed position on right side of content area

LAYOUT:
[Panel 1: 280px] [Main Content: Flexible] [Panel 2: 260px (if applicable)]

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[7.2] TABLET (768px - 1279px)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

PANEL 1 (PRIMARY):
├─ Hidden by default
├─ Slides in from left when menu button clicked
├─ Full width overlay appears
└─ Menu button visible at bottom (50px tall, #0d2532)

PANEL 2 (SECONDARY):
├─ Always hidden (display: none)
└─ Not enough screen width for two sidebars

LAYOUT:
[Main Content: Full Width]
[Menu Button: Fixed at bottom]

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[7.3] MOBILE (< 768px)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

PANEL 1 (PRIMARY):
├─ Hidden by default
├─ Slides in from left when menu button clicked
├─ Full width overlay appears
└─ Menu button visible at bottom

PANEL 2 (SECONDARY):
├─ Always hidden
└─ No room for secondary navigation

LAYOUT:
[Main Content: Full Width, Single Column]
[Menu Button: Fixed at bottom]

